node.text:
Innovation runs on open source. See how GitHub Enterprise helps businesses build their best software with the world's best code and communities. 
And check out some behind the scenes fun from making this piece!

node.text: Octoverse is awesome not only because of all of the data, but because of the extraordinary design work! @gladwearefriends created the site's design and @frederique.png created the illustrations. #dataviz #design #designer #illustration #data #githubdesign

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by GitHub on April 03, 2019. Image may contain: possible text that says '7 The State of the Octoverse 1/'

node.text: This Octocat of the Week is Kimonocat! @tonytimetables illustrated her to be as multi-talented and dangerous as she is beautiful—watch out for that sword! #design #illustration #illustrator #githubdesign #octocat

A lot goes on behind the scenes! Check out all the hard work that took place to go from raw footage to finished animation for the video "What is GitHub?". The collaboration between video and animation teams at GitHub made this awesome clip possible. #animation #video #behindthescenes #design #illustration #githubdesign
Yeehaw! It is only fitting to have Rodeotocat Mona, designed by @jeej.kang, riding a *sea*horse. #githubdesign #designer #illustration #illustrator

Meet the Blacktocats! This highly popular sticker design is comprised of multiple individual Blacktocats, each with their own unique style and personality, each illustrated by @cameronfoxly. #githubdesign #illustration #illustrator #stickers #design

node.text: Be proud of who you love. GitHub’s PRIDE shirts, by @rubyjazzdesign, aren’t only great to look at and wear—they do good too. Sales of these tees raised roughly $10k for LGBTQ+ charities.

node.text:
Mona’s in the mood! Illustrator @heyhaleycarroll created Cupidtocat, the perfect octocat for Valentine’s week.
#githubdesign #illustration #illustrator #designer

For GitHub Universe 2018, the team brought an interactive, colorable Mona—the Blanktocat—to life. @wodzgn crafted the pose, sketches, and initial 3D models then @_omar_hesham created the 3D model, and @rubyjazzdesign created the colorful package design.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by GitHub on February 08, 2019. Image may contain: 1 person

node.text: During September we hid an "easter egg"—a cypher hidden in JavaScript—in our "Building the Future" video. The cypher key was written in the code shown in the video itself 👀. When decoded, it unlocked a FREE trip to GitHub Universe 2018! Colin D'Souza, of Toronto was the first to solve our little puzzle and win the prize 🎉
